        <h2 class="keditable"></h2>
        <div class="keditable" style="font-size: 22px;">Lathitha Development Centre, nestled in the heart of Mzamomhle, Gonubie, East London, stands as a beacon of hope and opportunity in a community grappling with adversity. With a population of approximately 40,000 residing within a relatively small geographic area, Mzamomhle faces staggering challenges, notably an estimated 80% unemployment rate among its residents. In response to this pressing need, Lathitha was established in 2012 with a steadfast commitment to effecting positive change and fostering self-sufficiency.<div><br></div><div>Since its inception, Lathitha has tirelessly pursued its mission through a multifaceted approach, combining skills training, work readiness programs, and holistic community engagement efforts. Our initiatives aim not only to address the immediate need for employment but also to empower individuals to build sustainable livelihoods and contribute meaningfully to society. Through programs such as computer training, Work For A Living, sewing, ABET Adult Learning, food gardening, educare, and street children homeschooling, Lathitha has played a pivotal role in equipping community members with the tools and knowledge needed to thrive in today's economy.</div><div><br></div><div>Beyond our core programs, Lathitha has embraced innovation and diversity in its offerings, reflecting our commitment to meeting the evolving needs of the community. From carpentry and building skills to shoe making, metalworking, English classes, math lessons, food gardens, and rabbit raising, our supplementary initiatives provide additional avenues for skill development and personal growth. By nurturing a culture of lifelong learning and empowerment, Lathitha continues to make a tangible difference in the lives of individuals and families across Mzamomhle.</div><div><br></div><div>As we look towards the future, Lathitha remains steadfast in its dedication to fostering positive change and uplifting the community of Mzamomhle. By working hand in hand with residents, stakeholders, and partners, we are committed to building a brighter, more prosperous future for all. Together, we will continue to empower individuals, transform communities, and create lasting impact that transcends generations.<br></div></div>

